From a cost perspective, we=E2=80=99d have to guess that this sensor array =
costs Waymo upwards of $40-50K for each vehicle, not including the other se=
nsors we could not assess, or the additional onboard compute, wiring harnes=
ses, etc required to install and run it. And we should note that the LiDAR =
units are manufactured by Waymo, so costs would likely be even greater if s=
ourced from a third party vendor.

The latest Teslas are taking a very different approach, relying on vision c=
ompletely, with seven external cameras (plus one focused on the driver); th=
is obviously costs a lot less, and equally obviously, it=E2=80=99s a lot le=
ss robust. That=E2=80=99s why even the latest Tesla self-driving update is =
only Level 2 autonomy (the vehicle can perform steering and acceleration, b=
ut the human still monitors all tasks and can =E2=80=94 and may be required=
 to =E2=80=94 take control at any time), while Waymo is Level 4 (the vehicl=
e performs all driving tasks under specific conditions and within geofences=
, and human override is possible =E2=80=94 and in the case of Waymo, done r=
emotely).

