Tesla Self-Driving 12.5
-----------------------

I did get a chance to ride-along in a Tesla with the latest 12.5 self-drivi=
ng update on my recent trip, and I was pretty impressed! The ride was very =
smooth, and the car handled both city streets and highway driving with aplo=
mb, including managing one particularly tricky situation on a narrow side s=
treet with an illegally parked vehicle and oncoming traffic. I would even g=
o so far as to say that I preferred the Tesla=E2=80=99s driving style more =
than the Waymo=E2=80=99s, which sometimes felt frustratingly over-cautious =
and robot-like (your mileage may vary).

That noted, there was a driver behind the wheel, and that driver-focused ca=
mera I referenced above is there to ensure the driver is always looking ahe=
ad, and not, say, at their phone. From what I understand the camera can be =
fooled by sunglasses, or you could mount your phone in front of you, but ul=
timately the idea is that you as a driver should be engaged with the trip, =
even if you=E2=80=99re not doing anything most of the time.

And, I must note, the driver was necessary on at least one occasion: the Te=
sla didn=E2=80=99t make a driving error per se, but rather it was in the wr=
ong lane in a road that was splitting, which means it was on the verge of m=
aking a wrong turn. Maybe it would have caught itself, but it was rapidly a=
pproaching the point where such a catch would have been dangerous in its ow=
n right, so the driver took control and changed lanes. This did all happen =
quite naturally, and the Tesla interface asked for voice feedback on why th=
e disengagement happened, but it was still an error.

From an experiential perspective, having a driver there did change the feel=
ing of the experience; this was a cool demonstration, but nothing close to =
the =E2=80=9CWow!=E2=80=9D factor of Waymo. There is something that is tang=
ible =E2=80=94 or I guess intangible =E2=80=94 about there being no one beh=
ind the wheel. It=E2=80=99s also possible that all of the visible sensors o=
n the Waymo are comforting, although you don=E2=80=99t really see them when=
 you=E2=80=99re in the car. That noted, the experience was good enough that=
, were I to move to some place like Los Angeles where we were, I would cert=
ainly want to have a Tesla of my own.

Still, there=E2=80=99s a pretty big gulf to Level 4 and Robotaxis; given th=
at, I=E2=80=99m very curious to see what exactly will be announced tomorrow=
.

